  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6989 sitting right below the massive 7000 gamma wall (16.6B) in PIN regime, dealers are actively selling this rally attempt as they hedge their long gamma positions. The -3.7% to -4.2% recent weakness suggests dealers successfully capped upside momentum at 7000, and with spot now between the 6975 (5.4B) and 7000 walls, expect continued two-way flow but with a downside bias toward the GEX flip at 6887. Key resistance remains the 7000-7025-7050 gamma wall cluster above, while any break below 6887 flips dealers short gamma and accelerates selling pressure toward 6800 max negative gamma.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect selling pressure to keep price capped below 7000 with downside risk toward 6887.",
